This fix initializes the `bbox` variable to zeros, preventing the use-of-uninitialized-value error. The uninitialized `bbox` could contain arbitrary values from memory, which would cause undefined behavior when passed to functions expecting properly initialized rectangle structures. By explicitly initializing it to zero values, we ensure predictable behavior.